name: 3D Design, Augmented and Virtual Reality – Wize Academy
desc: Children use the Co-Spaces EDU tool to create AR/VR interactive content and learn coding. They will explore the creation of virtual tours, storytelling, games and simulations in multiple dimensions (3D, voiceover, music, video). Program offered in collaboration with Wize Academy.
age_description: Age at least 6 yrs but less than 14 yrs,

desc: Create your own 3D worlds, choosing characters and enemies to program your game. Three different PC games that can be taken home and shared. Software to create your own games at home. Half-day of computer and half-day camp activities.

name: 3D Modeling Factory
desc: Learn skills in 3D modeling and animation. Gain new skills in modeling characters and see how projects can be brough into a 3D game and how to animate them.

name: 3D Modeling Factory
desc: Learn skills in 3D modeling and animation. Gain new skills in modeling characters and see how projects can be brought into a 3D game and how to animate them.

name: Advanced Leadership Program
desc: Get job ready. Team building, communication, programming and leadership skills. Complete Standard First Aid/CPR 'C'/AED, High Five and ALP certificates. Includes an outing and placement in City of Ottawa program. 40+ eligible hours for secondary school community involvement.
age_description: Age at least 14 yrs but less than 18 yrs,

name: Adventures at Stevens Creek Farm
desc: Enjoy a fun week on the farm. Learn about farm tools, chores, and how to care for animals. Finish the week off with an introductory riding lesson. Mornings will be spent at the farm and afternoons will be at the community centre participating in fun camp games and activities. Camp offered in collaboration with Stevens Creek Farm.
age_description: Age at least 10 yrs but less than 15 yrs,

name: Club d'activités parascolaires annuel – Après l'école
desc: Terminez votre journée d'école en vous amusant. Soyez actifs en participant à des jeux et à des sports et soyez créatifs en vous adonnant à des activités artistiques et à du bricolage, tout en profitant de périodes de tranquillité pour faire vos devoirs. Faites-vous de nouveaux amis en adhérant au programme d'après l'école. La Ville d'Ottawa est un organisme accrédité HIGH FIVE®. La Ville d'Ottawa s'est engagée à assurer le sain développement des enfants et à leur offrir des programmes de loisirs sécuritaires. Faites le choix de la qualité pour vos enfants.

name: Coding with Micro:bits – Virtual – Child
location: Virtual - Zoom Meeting, link to follow via email
desc: Learn how to program computers using a mini-computer that fits in the palm of your hand. Create games, musical instruments, science projects, and other fun activities using a BBC Micro:bit. Requires a personal electronic device with an internet connection. Supply kits will be available for pickup before the start of classes.
age_description: Age at least 9 yrs but less than 15 yrs,

name: Coding with Minecraft Education – Wize Academy
desc: Children will use Microsoft Minecraft Education Software. Introduction to computational thinking, basic coding concepts, sequencing and patterning, variables and coordinates, debugging and troubleshooting, computational thinking in the real world and final project. Program offered in collaboration with Wize Academy.
age_description: Age at least 6 yrs but less than 14 yrs,

name: Congé de mars - Camp d'Ottawa aventure
desc: Apportez toute votre énergie au camp pour profiter des journées d’aventure et de plaisirs avec vos nouveaux amis. Il y aura des sports, des jeux, du bricolage, des activités spéciales et, bien entendu, une sortie amusante! (La sortie pourrait comprendre une séance de baignade).

name: Couleurs aquatiques 1 - Jaune
desc: Votre enfant apprendra à flotter et à glisser de façon autonome sur le ventre et sur le dos, et à entrer dans l'eau peu profonde et à en sortir. De plus, votre enfant apprendra les techniques de respiration sous l'eau. À la fin de ce cours, votre enfant pourra nager sur une distance d'au moins cinq mètres.

De plus, votre enfant apprendra les techniques de respiration sous l'eau. À la fin de ce cours, votre enfant pourra nager sur une distance d'au moins cinq mètres.
age_description: Age at least 6 yrs but less than 15 yrs,

name: Couleurs aquatiques 10 - Lime
desc: Votre enfant apprendra le crawl tête haute et la brasse tête haute, le saut compact et l'intervention en cas d'étouffement. Votre enfant continuera à améliorer le crawl, le dos crawlé, la brasse, la marinière et la nage élémentaire sur le dos. À la fin de ce cours, votre enfant pourra effectuer une nage chronométrée de 400 mètres en 13 minutes.

name: Game Design and Development with Roblox® – Wize Academy
desc: Video game design is comprised of many different technical and abstract components and in this program, children will learn basic Lua programming while they develop a game project. We provide a constructive and safe space for students to learn and apply the same concepts that real life programmers and game designers use to create video games. As your child codes and taps into their critical thinking skills, they’ll be able to see the results of their programming by watching their game transform. Camp offered in collaboration with Wize Academy.

name: Game Developer Extreme
desc: 2D games continue to be popularly on mobile platforms. Make your own video game. Learn the creative game-making process from design stage to completion. Games can be exported to any platform; MacOS, Windows or mobile. Create a complex, realistic video game with your own graphics or provided graphics. User-friendly exciting and challenging, it's perfect for the aspiring game designer or whose who love to play games and see how they're made. It's the perfect springboard from Scratch to Unity Game Design.

desc: Build real and virtual LEGO® projects at home using the new LEGO set provided and a home computer. Learn LEGO building techniques as you construct several mechanical Technic projects. Develop a Technic project. Learn to use LEGO Studio 2.0, a LEGO CAD program, build a variety of virtual engineering and architecture projects. Build a virtual LEGO MinecraftTM project. Create online instructions for a Technic build. Render virtual LEGO® projects to look incredibly real. Using a virtual robot, learn to code and simulate robot sounds and movements online. Perform maze navigation as well as object and colour detection challenges. Learn about electronic concepts, components and circuits, and breadboard in a safe virtual environment. Requires a PC or MacTM, laptop or desktop computer (not a ChromebookTM) to run Studio 2.0 and connect to Zoom®. Download and install Studio 2.0 prior to the first class. More information provided at registration. Includes LEGO set - available for pickup before the start of classes. In collaboration with ‘the LEGO® guy,’ Ian Dudley of Orange STEM Education, www.orangestem.ca.

name: Médaille de Bronze et secourisme d'urgence avec RCR-B
desc:
Conditions préalables : Étoile de bronze ou avoir 13 ans au moment de l'examen.

Ce cours apprend aux candidats à intervenir dans des situations complexes de sauvetage aquatique. Il améliore la condition physique, la prise de décisions et l'esprit critique des candidats afin de les préparer à des sauvetages difficiles, de risques accrus. Les candidats acquerront une meilleure technique de nage et amélioreront leur endurance lors d'une nage chronométrée.

name: Swim Explorer
desc:
Improve your skills and strokes with daily lessons from the Swim City Program and leisure swim time. Camp activities each day.

Shared Care Support: The City of Ottawa is committed to the inclusion of all campers. To best support children at camp, please make us aware of any diagnosed or undiagnosed cognitive differences or behaviours your child may have early on. Making us aware early on will help our coordinators arrange for any additional supports that may be needed. If your child requires integration support at school, please contact the Inclusive Recreation team at InclusiveRecreation-LoisirsInclusifs@ottawa.ca. 1:1 Shared Care support can be offered at no cost for 2 weeks. Please be advised that Shared Care is based on a first-come, first-served basis. Please reach out early to secure your spot and allow enough time for the intake process prior to the start of camp. Camp participation criteria will be used to determine eligibility for Shared Care support.

This does not guarantee a place in private lessons.  Please note you must have completed an in-water assessment with Inclusive Recreation in order to participate in this program.  For more information please contact inclusiverecreation-loisirsinclusifs@ottawa.ca
age_description: Age at least 3 yrs but less than 18 yrs,

name: Swimming – Private Lessons – Inclusive Recreation Waitlist
desc: This is a waitlist for Inclusive Recreation private swim lessons at Richcraft Recreation centre for Winter 2024. The date and time of this waitlist are not the course date or time.  Lessons times and days will vary.  This does not guarantee a place in private lessons.  Please note you must have completed an in-water assessment with Inclusive Recreation in order to participate in this program.  For more information please contact inclusiverecreation-loisirsinclusifs@ottawa.ca
age_description: Age at least 3 yrs but less than 18 yrs,

name: Étoile de bronze
desc:
Le candidat doit être capable de nager aisément et de façon continue sur une distance minimum de 300 m.

Ce niveau prépare les candidats aux nages chronométrées, aux sauvetages et aux techniques de sauvetage. D’autres compétences en secourisme sont enseignées. Excellent pour ceux qui veulent prendre leur médaille de bronze et qui n'ont pas 13 ans.
age_description: Age at least 10 yrs but less than 15 yrs,
